# Platform Web Performance & Infrastructure Standards

Every client app (`apps/*`) must meet this checklist. When migrating a new client or scaffolding a brand, bring it to this standard before launch. The reference implementation is **`apps/northbound-treatment`** (best-tuned config) — copy its patterns, do not invent new ones.

For metadata / canonical / robots / sitemap / revalidate rules, `platform-seo-infrastructure.mdc` is the source of truth — this rule does not override it.

## A. Rendering & routing
- Marketing pages are **Server Components** (SSG/ISR) — never `"use client"` at the page root.
- Internal navigation uses **`next/link`**, never raw `<a href="/...">` for in-app routes.
- Blog index + `[slug]` keep `export const revalidate = 3600` + `generateStaticParams`. Never `force-dynamic`.
- Legacy/WP URL changes go through **`redirects()`** (301) in `next.config.ts`, not client-side redirects.
- `trailingSlash` must match how the live domain is indexed in Search Console and be consistent with sibling brands sharing that URL convention.

## B. Image optimization (most common migration gap)
- **Zero raw `<img>` on marketing pages** — always `next/image`. (Exception: WP-migrated `blog_posts` body HTML.)
- `next.config.ts` `images` MUST enable AVIF and cap device sizes. AVIF is **not** on by default — opt in:

```ts
images: {
  remotePatterns: [{ protocol: "https", hostname: "<ref>.supabase.co" }],
  formats: ["image/avif", "image/webp"],
  deviceSizes: [640, 750, 828, 1080, 1200, 1280],
  imageSizes: [16, 32, 48, 64, 96, 128, 256, 384],
},
```

- LCP hero gets `priority`; below-the-fold images lazy-load (default).
- Every `<Image>` has explicit `sizes` + `width`/`height` (or `fill` + a sized container) to prevent CLS.
- Remove stray migration CDNs (squarespace, readdy, etc.) from `remotePatterns` once images are re-hosted on Supabase.

## C. Fonts & icons
- Fonts via **`next/font`** (self-hosted, no render-block, no layout shift) — never a Google `<link>`.
- Prefer a **self-hosted Remix Icon subset** (see `apps/northbound-treatment/scripts/build-remixicon-subset.mjs`) over a render-blocking CDN `<link>`.

## D. JS / bundle
- `serverExternalPackages: ["@cursor/sdk"]` in every `next.config.ts`.
- `experimental.optimizePackageImports: ["@sweetmedia/admin-core", "@sweetmedia/blog-core"]`.
- Heavy/interactive-only widgets (forms, carousels, maps, modals) load via **`next/dynamic`**.

## E. Build, security & monitoring
- `typescript.ignoreBuildErrors: false`.
- Block `/admin` from indexing with both `robots.ts` disallow AND an `X-Robots-Tag` header:

```ts
async headers() {
  return [{ source: "/admin/:path*", headers: [
    { key: "X-Robots-Tag", value: "noindex, nofollow, noarchive" },
  ]}];
},
```

- `@vercel/analytics` + `@vercel/speed-insights` wired; `postbuild` runs `sync-tracked-pages.ts`.

## Rollout rule
Fix `apps/client-template` first so every future brand inherits the standard, then bring existing brands in sync. PPC landers intentionally marked `robots: { index: false }` are exempt from the dynamic-metadata requirement.
